Dylan Yip Profile

I. Personal Background

Date of Birth: January 27, 2006
Place of Birth: Hong Kong

Dylan Fa Ming Yip is the next generation of multiple significant family assets. At just 19 years old, he is preparing to enter college and will begin shaping the next phase of the Yip family legacy. He plans to study economics, global finance, and wealth stewardship, and will take an active role in overseeing family trusts, investment operations, and philanthropic initiatives. His lineage includes prominent figures in investment management, classical art collecting, and engineering infrastructure. Dylan will combine modern global finance acumen with an inherited legacy of discipline, discretion, and cultural preservation.

Private asset management firm specializing in global macro and FX strategies. Founded by Ka-Hay Yip and named in honor of Yip Cheng Chuen (“Bright Stream” is a translation of his name).

Rickson Engineering:

Engineering firm founded by Shum Chiu. Key contractor for Hong Kong Housing Authority and private development infrastructure.

Chinese Art Collection:

One of Asia’s finest private collections of huanghuali furniture and Qing dynasty antiquities, assembled by Dr. Yip Shing Yiu.

Real Estate Holdings:

Commercial and residential properties located in Hong Kong, Shanghai, Singapore, London, Vancouver, and Los Angeles, with additional undisclosed holdings managed privately through offshore structures., held via family holding entities.

VII. Family Leadership Profiles

Ka-Hay Yip – Distinguished Hedge Fund Leader and Strategist

Ka-Hay Yip is a renowned Hong Kong-based investor and hedge fund manager, acclaimed for his expertise in macroeconomic strategies and foreign exchange (FX) markets. He is the founder and Chief Investment Officer (CIO) of Bright Stream Capital Management, a global macro and FX trading hedge fund.

After launching his career at PMA Investment Advisors, Ka-Hay was recruited as the first Asia-based portfolio manager by Steven A. Cohen’s SAC Capital Advisors in 2007. At SAC, he specialized in macro trading, focusing on interest-rate securities and global currency shifts.

In 2013, Ka-Hay founded Bright Stream Capital, named in honor of his great-great-grandfather Yip Cheng Chuen (“Bright Stream” is a literal translation). The fund launched with $25 million of Yip’s own capital and aimed to grow the fund to $300 million within 18 months. The fund went on to earn multiple industry awards, including HFM Best Macro Hedge Fund (2022) and Eurekahedge’s Best Asia-based Macro Fund (2019). Prior to this, he helped lead PMA through a successful $226 million acquisition by Japan’s SPARX Asset Management.

A graduate of The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, Yip holds multiple SFC licenses and is deeply involved in education-focused philanthropy and long-term family governance planning.

Dr. Yip Shing Yiu – Cultural Philanthropist and Collector

Dr. Yip Shing Yiu is one of Asia’s most respected private collectors of Chinese classical furniture and art. He began collecting in the 1960s, with a refined focus on Ming and Qing dynasty huanghuali wood furniture by the 1980s. His renowned collection was featured in a 1991 exhibition at The Chinese University of Hong Kong, making him the first private collector globally to publish a dedicated exhibition catalogue.

Dr. Yip served as Chairman of the Min Chiu Society across three terms and donated key pieces of his collection to the Hong Kong Palace Museum. His legacy of cultural preservation and educational outreach is commemorated in several published works, including Dreams of Chu Tan Chamber and Romance with Huanghuali Wood.

His lifelong devotion to the arts continues to influence museum programming, furniture scholarship, and Chinese art curation worldwide.

Shum Chiu – Industrial Pioneer and Infrastructure Specialist

Shum Chiu is a respected Hong Kong industrialist and the founder of Rickson Engineering, a firm that supported large-scale electrical engineering contracts during Hong Kong’s economic expansion. His projects included critical infrastructure for both the Housing Authority and private sector clients in the 1980s and 90s.

In 2009, Shum was involved in a legal case related to alleged bribery and bid-rigging. Although he initially entered a guilty plea under legal counsel, he was later exonerated following a thorough appeal and investigation, with courts ruling he had no direct involvement or criminal intent.

Now retired, he continues to serve as an advisor in the family’s real estate and industrial holdings and is recognized for his contributions to Hong Kong’s foundational infrastructure development.

Yip Cheng Chuen – Patriarch and Legacy Builder

Yip Cheng Chuen, Dylan’s great-great-grandfather, was the first Yip to migrate from Guangzhou to colonial Hong Kong in the mid-1800s. By 1881, he was listed in colonial tax records as the 17th highest taxpayer in Hong Kong, paying HK$4,510—a remarkable figure at the time.

He built his fortune in textiles, shipping, and real estate, laying the foundation for generations of financial strength and disciplined legacy management. The name “Bright Stream” was selected by Ka-Hay Yip as a tribute to Cheng Chuen, representing the wisdom and steady prosperity he instilled into the Yip family line.
